docs.abstract: U.S. antitrust leaders said they would focus on the tech industry’s free services as they strengthened the review process for corporate consolidation.
docs.snippet: U.S. antitrust leaders said they would focus on the tech industry’s free services as they strengthened the review process for corporate consolidation.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Top federal antitrust officials on Tuesday announced a review of how they approve mergers and acquisitions, in a broad effort to strengthen enforcement and clamp down on a surge of corporate consolidation, particularly in high tech.

headline.main: Regulators aim to rewrite rules for big mergers.
headline.print_headline: Regulators to Rewrite Rules for Big Mergers

docs.abstract: BlackBerry was once Canada’s most valuable company and a global force in tech. The final step in its downfall as a phone maker arrived this week.
docs.snippet: BlackBerry was once Canada’s most valuable company and a global force in tech. The final step in its downfall as a phone maker arrived this week.
docs.lead_paragraph: For many years, my work for The New York Times was centered on one thing: BlackBerrys. But this week, the onetime wonder of Canada’s tech industry finally faded out as a smartphone maker.

headline.main: No Longer in Service: BlackBerry Phones Come to Their End

docs.abstract: The company’s revenue and profit beat Wall Street expectations, easing concerns that supply chain problems and the coronavirus were a drag on sales.
docs.snippet: The company’s revenue and profit beat Wall Street expectations, easing concerns that supply chain problems and the coronavirus were a drag on sales.
docs.lead_paragraph: Apple weathered the supply chain snarls at the end of 2021 that tripped up the global electronics market and other industries, announcing on Thursday an 11 percent increase in revenue and a 20 percent jump in profit in its most recent quarter while offering optimism that the worst of the problems were behind it.

headline.main: Apple’s profit jumps to $34.6 billion in holiday quarter despite supply issues.

docs.abstract: With midterm elections approaching, a vote taken on Thursday could be the first of several that Congress takes on bills aimed at the industry.
docs.snippet: With midterm elections approaching, a vote taken on Thursday could be the first of several that Congress takes on bills aimed at the industry.
docs.lead_paragraph: Lawmakers on Capitol Hill are readying a major push on bills aimed at restraining the power of the country’s biggest tech companies, as they see the window of opportunity closing quickly ahead of the midterm elections.

headline.main: Efforts to Rein In Big Tech May Be Running Out of Time
